explanation: This solution iterates over the string a and checks for each prefix if it is a subsequence of b and if it is not a subsequence of b. If such a prefix is found, it is returned as the longest uncommon subsequence. If no such prefix is found, it means that every subsequence of a is also a subsequence of b, so -1 is returned.

